tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated hemoglobin (15.9 g/dL; upper limit 15.5 g/dL), which may reflect mild hemoconcentration or individual variation. No evidence of anemia, infection, electrolyte imbalance, or renal dysfunction. Overall, the laboratory profile is unremarkable and stable. Clinical correlation is recommended.
